The Economic and Financial Crimes Commission (EFCC) Lagos Zonal office, on Friday, May 11, arrested over 12 suspected internet fraudsters popularly known as ‘Yahoo Boys’ during a raid Club 57 in the Ikoyi area of Lagos. The agency confirmed the raid in a statement on its Facebook page. The statement it also issued on Twitter reads: The post EFCC Raids Club 57 In Ikoyi, Arrests 12 ‘Yahoo Boys’ appeared first on 360Nobs.com.   Follow us on twitter @NigeriaTodayNG Also, Like us on facebook This post was syndicated from 360Nobs.com. Click here to read the full text on the original website.